<Base path="/about" title="About" description="ArtempireMJ is a global art institution that tells the world through artists.">
  <section class="wrap prose" style="padding-block: clamp(2rem,6vw,4rem) 3rem;">
    <p class="eyebrow">The institution</p>
    <h1>The world, told through artists.</h1>
    <p class="lede">You already follow the world. The elections and the currencies, the migrations
      and the music, the things that move a place. ArtempireMJ brings it to you through the artists
      who live inside those stories. The world is what you came for. The artist is how you see it new.</p>

    <h2>Who it serves</h2>
    <p class="muted">Artists first. Emerging, mid-career, maker-adjacent. The calendar, the
      features, and the radar are theirs, mostly free. The soul of the place is the artists in it
      and the readers who come for them.</p>

    <h2>The correspondents</h2>
    <p class="muted">On-the-ground access, region by region. Khethiwe Tracy Gumede reports from
      South Africa. Kathleen Mureithi carries Money Stories. The network grows by city.
      <a href="/correspondents">Report from yours.</a></p>
    <figure style="margin:1.2rem 0 0;">
      <img src="/images/khethiwe_tshabalala_bkhz_at_joburg.jpg" alt="A gallery presentation at FNB Art Joburg"
        width="1200" height="800" loading="lazy" decoding="async"
        style="width:100%;height:auto;border-radius:4px;aspect-ratio:3/2;object-fit:cover;" />
      <figcaption class="muted" style="margin-top:0.5rem;font-size:0.85rem;">BKhz at FNB Art Joburg. Photograph by Khethiwe Tracy Gumede, our correspondent in South Africa.</figcaption>
    </figure>

    <h2>Who runs it</h2>
    <p class="muted">ArtempireMJ is founder-run. Morris Javan built it to do one thing well, to tell
      the world through the artists who live it, and he keeps the eye steady from behind the work.
      When he appears in it, it is as one maker among the many the institution covers. The artists
      carry the story. He makes sure it gets told.</p>

    <p style="margin-top:2rem;"><a class="btn ghost" href="/">See the calendar</a></p>
  </section>
</Base>
